Definition: physics) an effect whereby a body moving in a rotating frame of reference experiences the Coriolis force acting perpendicular to the direction of motion and to the axis of rotation
Example: on Earth the Coriolis effect deflects moving bodies to the right in the northern hemisphere and to the left in the southern hemisphere
Synonyms: consequence, noun, cognition, physics, c, an, effect, whereby, a, body, moving, in, rotating, frame, of, reference, experiences, the, Coriolis, force, acting, perpendicular, to, direction, motion, and, axis, rotation, on, Earth, deflects, bodies, right, northern, hemisphere, left, southern
Category: noun.phenomenon
